At line 149-162, it checks for clients:
```javascript
if (this.clients?.claude) {
  providerPromises.push(...);
}
if (this.clients?.gemini) {
  providerPromises.push(...);
}
if (this.clients?.local) {
  providerPromises.push(...);
}
```

If none of the clients are initialized, it would return "No AI providers available".

But wait - looking at the orchestrator.js again:
- Line 64-68: ClaudeClient is initialized
- Line 70-74: LocalModelClient is initialized
- Line 76-81: GeminiClient is ONLY initialized if `this.config.geminiProject` exists

And from the .env file, I don't see GCP_PROJECT set. So Gemini is likely not configured. But Claude should be.

